items.text: Good food good deserts
Try the King Prawns Alio Olio
The superfood salad might just be the best salad I've ever had at a restaurant.
Nice café in French style.
Portobello mushrooms burger with truffle fries rocks! Maybe the best vegetarian burger ever.
Great place for brunch, eggs benedict and Steak Sandwich are Highly Recommended as well as the truffle fries.
Had a lovely afternoon tea with friends as the desserts were really yummy. Especially the puddings. But is a high-end pricey place worth going though.
truffle Fries are to die for!!
My second favourite ps cafe
For dessert chocolate cake is pretty good but be prepared.. Is just a chocolate cake with a chocolate sauce and ice cream
The portion is sooo big! IMO chicken in a basket can feed 2 people. So full!
Try the truffle fries!
Gado gado salad 👍 service needs improvement
Cozy environment and great place hang out with friends
Try their digestive tea!!
Beautiful airy space. As with all other PS cafés, this one is green and charming. Decent food too. Great for tête-à-tête brunches.
The wagyu burger disappointing. Very dry and lack of seasoning. Its a bit burnt too.
I like the atmosphere of the place. Clean and not very crowded on a weekday evening.
Yes, the truffle shoestring fries are the best!!! Green apple mojito is refreshing too
Tried the steak sandwich and aglio olio pasta. Would recommend the steak sandwich!! My usual is the green goddess pesto penne which is really awesome too!
Quiet, excellent staff, great place to read or date.
If you ever make a reservation with them do bear in mind that minimum orders has to be 1 side n 3 main course
This is my fav P.S cafe and the food is very good.
Have the leftover lasagne.  It's amazing!
Used to be good but popped by here for lunch and I was left a bit disappointed at what I got for the price I paid :(
When I'm not getting the superfood salad I'm looking at the other salads with truffle fries
You get quantity and quality food & quality atmosphere with a hefty price tag and wait times. However I suspect that they re-use leftovers because waiter didn't pack my salad when I asked them to...
Arrive early for Sunday Brunch on the patio - fruit platter is great for sharing, brunch burger rocks!
Tried the Blueberry & Banana Pancakes ($24++) as well as Dark Chocolate Banana Cheesecake ($16++/slice). Was not impressed by the taste but by the price 😑
Pair the chicken in a basket with the Asian slaw (ikr?) and have a beautiful flavour explosion in your pleb mouth.
Sangria great! And one of the few places to do cheese platter. And the staff are smart, nice people
Great ambience. Try it!

It's all about the truffle fries!! They're about $15 but you do get a mountain of beautiful crispy fries. Perfect place to sit with a book, coffee & a slice of cake. Pick the outdoor covered terrace!!
Just a great place period! You'll always find something here... The food is good not great!
Go for a mid-week dinner on the outdoor balcony and escape the weekend brunch madness. Try the pork curry and a fresh mango/mint soda. The truffle fries are better at House, Dempsey.
Yeppp chicken in a basket! And frieeeessss lotsa carbssss!!!!
Just eat the truffle fries. I end up caving and ordering them every time! They are just THAT good.
It's always nice here. The cakes especially. But brunch items like the eggs etc are nice too!
A trip to PS Cafe won't be complete without an order of truffle fries.
Great interiors. Sticky date pudding is highly recommended! Read more at http://candidcuisine.net/ps-cafe-palais-renaissance-singapore/
Big Nihon salad was appetizing, the Moroccan lamb was wonderful and the ginger pudding served with earl grey sauce + vanilla ice cream was amazing. I never expected this combi to work so well! <3
Miso cod is decent. Quite fresh. But the pumpkin wasn't fresh, salad was good.
love the truffle friess! Ask for lala, she's polite, attentive and awesome!
Nice ambience but I don't think the food is worth the price.
LOVE the truffle fries. Make sure u order it when u are here!
Cozy. Food served in generous portion. Try their PS Lasagna & Moroccan Lamb.. 
They love to make you wait 20min for a table just to ensure that there is a long waiting queue, while having "dirty" idle tables available and nobody to clean them.
Get their sticky date pudding. Each person has to order one dish though
FRENCH FRIES!!!
Bring back the Spagetti Bolognese
Everything
Try the breakfast brulee...if you're into sweet starts. Otherwise, best croque madame in town!
all food is best！！！
Truffle Fries are to die for here!!
Very good breakfast!
The place is nt that good. Shoe string fries are cold and hard..onion burger is tough and tasteless..steak sandwich is not bad
Great design, freshly cut nice food and cakes but slow service
Moroccan mutton and beef gnocci were delicious
Looking for the washrooms? It's through the non-descript green doors
The Miso Cod is really yummy! Soft and perfectly cooked!
Don't ever miss the truffle fries.
Sticky date dessert
Very modern french style cafe, coffee was ok, but nothing special, next time we will try some food or cakes! Look yummy!
Ribeye steak
Mushroom wellington is nice, healthy food wit lots of mushroom and veggi such as capsicum n carrot.
The burger is really good
Loved the truffle fries and cakes. Favourite is the carrot cake and the sticky date pudding is fantastic as well!
PS Cafe is a delicious refuge from the shopping noise of Orchard. Beautiful, light filled interior is a great setting for lively lunches. Bites are inventive and desserts are a must try.
الستيكي ديت + اللاتيه .... من الااااخر ، لعشاق الكوفي شوبات و الحلويات خلوا ستاربكس و جربوا هالكوفي
Fish & chips is a safe meal for most of the restaurant. But PS cafe also can ruined this "safe" taste. Feelingless meal, terrible service with this price, wow.
best place for brunch on a lazy saturday/sunday.
Great burger and caesar salad. The best choice is the steak sandwich and the fries( contain garlic).
Truffle fries and Chicken in a Basket.
A pretty nice place to chill out at. Indoor always seems to be fully reserved across all branches? Outdoor will be too hot😞 Rosé & Berries Sangria is too cute💕
Ambience is one of the best compared to their other outlets. Am so in love with their double chocolate cake.
Most of the desserts
Brunch burger left me unimpressed: questionable choice of ingredients (2cm thick onion ring, really?) and very bland patty, basically tasteless. Desserts, on the other hand, are top-notch.
Chicken in a basket is a must!  And replace regular fries with the truffle fries!
tasty prawn pasta👍
Surprised by the spicy chai latte! Very special!
Good brunch. Efficient staff despite the packed place. Was lucky with the friendly server. :)
My new love Thai salad
The fries and superfood salad is great. They have many healthy options.
I came here expecting good fries. The fries tasted like McDonald's fries with Parmesan and truffle oil, and the burger was one of the worst we ever. Also the service was abysmal.
Coffee is good. Meal is value for money. Shakshouka is so tasty
Great ambient and food! I recommend you to stay outdoors, great music, tropical island ambient... Just sit there and enjoy.
Great decor, but overpriced. At such rates there should at least be free wifi. Pity not.
Dessert wins over the brunch main course.
My favorite Cafe! Great food! fabulous ambience!! love the decor!!
Nice ambiance. Great food. Truffle fries is the best!
Nice place but service here isn't very good. Pricey too.
Truffle fries are YUM. Huge portion!
The desserts are to die for but very rich. Even if you have a sweet tooth, share one portion with a friend because chances are you won't be able to finish it.
Great venue with indoor and outdoor seating. Beautiful and feels secluded (although it's right on the heart of Orchard)
Come for truffle fries. Leave happy.
Truffle Fries !! Must try their dessert next time !!
Their specials are actually rather special
nihon salad was good - quite expensive though. Basket of chicken was overrated. great decor though
There's a minimum order of one main course per person during dinner. It's enclosed and noisy. I would much prefer the Harding Road outlet.
Truffle fries = good
Great food. Great staff. Great ambient.
The chocolate black-out cake is such an indulgence!
Lovely place for brunch or afternoon smoothies! Get a place outdoor...
Very nice place and very good atmosphere, but come on Singapore, 30 bucks for an ok Burger, are you kidding me?
Had dinner with Frens earlier.. The ambience is cozy!! Like it!!
Still delivering quality food after so many years.
Try the ginger pudding and fries!
Green apple mojito is lovely! Pricey though at $16 a pop before GST and service charge.
Great getaway from the bustle outside. Portions are huge - and get a load of the capsicum-flavoured water.
Reallllllllllly don't get the obsession with the truffle fries. Found them a huge disappointment. As previous reviewer said, cold and hard, definitely just frozen out of a bag.
Caesar with chicken and poached egg
Early dinner for two at 6pm, then staff says table is needed by 8pm. Who eats for 2 hours? Then still not done eating, 6:45, I look away to sneeze and waiter has hand on my plate ready to clear. WTF?
Truffle fan loves the truffle fries. You can smell it a (s)mile away. The PS chicken in a basket was fine. Tender. Blend of herbs made it unique.
Brunch burger is quite excellent.
Really great ambience and service! Food is good too. Worth the money!
Hard to fault them... Desserts are still yummy and the truffle fries don't disappoint. Price point creeps higher and higher though
Old-world ceiling fans give the place its charm but way too noisy to be enjoyable.
Truffle fries is really huge. Good for sharing if you have a large party. But I find that there's not enough truffle oil in it.
Truffle fries is not that WOW its normal frozen fries with nice cheese and truffle oil. I will not order again
Very disappointed with service staff. Not friendly upon arrive n forget told them abt birthday candle just a very simple to make a special day. Very bad don't be back and beef was bad anyway.
Pricey but good food and atmosphere. Can recommend salmon Benedict, and Brioche.
Must order: the truffle fries of course. Though I wish they had two sizes so we didn't have to stuff ourselves silly. The soy latte is very nice too. Seems pricey at $8 but so so worth it!
My favorite weekday place for a big slice of chocolate cake, drowned in chocolate sauce & ice-cream, and shared between friends. The bay windows, oscillating fans & tropical island interior do relax.
Love the garden ambience with a hothouse in the middle, it feels very old world with a café brunch menu to cater to all your whims - i like the bloody marys with my fries, then coffee & cake after.
Try Chicken in a Basket!! Sauces rock!
Carb Tart was done just nice, savory but not overwhelming. PS Burger ruined by the dry patty, big disappointment for $30. Great ambience though. 4Sq's price indicators is off, this is at least $$$.
One of the most beautiful cafes in Singapore and their steak sandwich is to die for!!!
Service is absolutely horrible
Не верьте foursquare, уровень цен здесь на все $$. Everything is rather tasty but overpriced😕 and unfortunately service needs upgrade
Miso cod, yum !
Friessssssss
Decent brunch. See dish recommendations and pictures at http://sparklette.net/food/ps-cafe-brunch/
The ribs and truffle fries are awesome!
Loved my blue swimmer crab & prawn omelette, let's face it the place is great, the food is brill, the truffles fries a must, just a shame it's so pricey!
The banana pudding is really good.
The fries, of course.
Breadboard is sufficiently generous for the price although I wish there were more dips.
Try the banana butterscotch cake with vanilla ice cream
Steak sandwich!!
Substitute smoked salmon from bacon was $3, 2 slices of salmon came. Wtf.
Take away 😋
The seaweed fries or whatever sucked. Tuna salad was good. Service seemed slightly overworked but relatively attentive for Singapore.
A great collection of papers and magazines which makes this a good spot for a business-person eating alone
Make sure you order the truffle fries!
Good food and service. Check out the alfresco seating if you want to get away from Singapore's wintery air conditioning
Try the big nihon salad, it's awesome.
Try the Steak Sandwich
I must say, P.S. Cafe has the best glass of water i've ever had. The burger is so good too!
Good food. Large servings. Can be shared.
Chicken In A Basket ~ 'nuff said
Cakes for sale by piece for dine in - 15/18 per dessert. high cakes, massive chocolate, carrot, meringue, banana cheesecake, lime pie
Here's a great place for a nice cup of tea and some cake on a weekend afternoon, tucked away from the hustle & bustle.
